Module de.learnlib.filter.reuse
Package de.learnlib.filter.reuse.tree

Class ReuseNode<S,​I,​O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.learnlib.filter.reuse.tree.ReuseNode<S,​I,​O>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - system state class
    I - input symbol class
    O - output symbol class
    public class ReuseNode<S,​I,​O>
extends Object
    A ReuseNode is a vertex in the ReuseTree that contains (a possibly empty) set of outgoing ReuseEdges. Each ReuseNode may contain a system state holding relevant information (e.g. database identifiers or an object) that belongs to the system state that 'represents' the system state after executing a membership query.
